}}},{"name":"1949-1980, 133 boxes.","recordType":["Papers"],"description":"The papers of West Virginia Congressman Harley O. Staggers include legislative files, correspondence, reports, bills, speeches, resolutions, news releases, and invitations. Legislation covers the following topics: banking, broadcasting, clean air, education, finance, international relations, the judiciary, public works, and trade. There also are records of the House Committee on Interstate and Foreign Commerce which Staggers chaired. A finding aid is available in the repository and online.","recordLocation":{"name":"West Virginia & Regional History Collection","location":{"addressLocality":"Morgantown","addressRegion":"WV"},"parentRecordLocation":{"name":"West Virginia University Libraries","location":{"addressLocality":"Morgantown","addressRegion":"WV"}}}}]}
